---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { site } from "../site.config";

const updated = "June 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description={`The simple terms for using ${site.name}, a free in-browser video compressor.`}
  path="/terms/"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-[760px] px-6 md:px-12 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.06em] text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-[var(--color-fg-subtle)]">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-8 text-[var(--color-fg-muted)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        By using {site.name} (the “Service”) you agree to these terms. They're meant to
        be fair and readable.
      </p>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">The Service</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          {site.name} is a free, browser-based video compressor. It runs on your device,
          processes your files locally, and requires no account. We offer it as-is for
          personal and commercial use.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Acceptable use</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Use the Service lawfully. Don't attempt to disrupt or abuse it, and don't use it
          with content that is illegal or infringes others' rights. You are responsible
          for the videos you compress and how you use the output.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Your content</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          Your videos are yours. Because they never leave your device, we claim no rights
          to them and have no access to them.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">No warranty</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          The Service is provided “as is,” without warranties of any kind. Compression is
          lossy by nature and results vary by source file, browser and device. We don't
          guarantee any particular output size, quality, speed, or format compatibility.
          Always keep your original file until you're happy with the result.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, {site.name} and its maker are not liable
          for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of
          the Service, including any loss of data or unsatisfactory output. You use it at
          your own discretion.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Governing law</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          These terms are governed by the laws of {site.jurisdiction}, without regard to
          conflict-of-law principles.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-fg)]">Changes & contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We may update these terms; the “last updated” date reflects any change.
          Questions? Email
          <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent)] underline">{site.contactEmail}</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
